DESCRIPTION:Join us on Saturday\, May 9\, from 1 - 3 PM at Whispering Vine Fourth St. for a tasting featuring 30+ Pinot Noir alongside passed flatbread from the Fourth St. kitchen.\nTasting Fee: $55 per person\nReserve your spot on Tock: https://www.exploretock.com/whisperingvine4thstreet\nFeatured Wines:\n- Kosta Browne Barrel Auction Pinot Noir 2021 – Winery $165 – Founded in 1997 by Dan Kosta and Michael Browne\, Kosta Browne has become a reference point for premium California Pinot Noir.\n- Rochioli Estate Pinot Noir 2021 – $99.99 – Rochioli is one of the benchmark names in Russian River Valley Pinot Noir\, farming estate vineyards that helped define the region for decades.\n- Paul Hobbs Russian River Pinot Noir 2023 – Winery $80 – Paul Hobbs is a world-renowned winemaker twice named Wine Personality of the Year by Robert Parker's Wine Advocate\, with a long track record for polished Russian River Pinot Noir.\n- Martinelli "Bondi Home Ranch" Russian River Valley Pinot Noir 2022 – Winery $85 – Martinelli is a fifth-generation Sonoma County family estate with more than 135 years of farming history\, producing site-specific wines from prized Russian River vineyards.\n- Louis Jadot Beaune Clos des Couchereaux Premier Cru 2023 – Winery $80 – Maison Louis Jadot\, founded in 1859\, is one of Burgundy's most respected houses\, known for wines that emphasize site\, structure and classic Côte d'Or character.\nCome explore 30+ Pinot Noir Wines and find your favorite bottle. Discover your favorite pour from the lineup.
LOCATION:4201 W Fourth St Reno\, NV 89523
SUMMARY:Passion for Pinot Party
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR